Package Exceptions

This package provides several exceptions which could be thrown in this project.

See: Description

  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    NumberType
    Created by phlippe on 25.06.17.
    PatternType
    Created by phlippe on 24.06.17.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ArgumentPatternException
    This class represents a basis structure for exceptions which are called by breaking a given pattern for arguments (e.g. email).
    DuplicateIDException
    This exception is thrown if an requirement should be created or its ID changed to a new ID which is already used by another requirement in the system.
    ListOverflowException
    This exception is thrown if a list has a greater size than the maximum value.
    MissingCostEstimationException
    This exception is thrown when a needed object of ICostEstimation is null because no estimation was created for the related requirement analysis.
    MissingFPException
    This exception is thrown if the function points are not calculated although the execution requires it.
    MissingReqAnException
    This exception is thrown when a needed object of IRequirementAnalysis is null.
    NumberOutOfBoundsException
    This exception is thrown if a number is not in the expected boundaries.
    StringNoNumberException
    This exception is thrown if a given string could not be converted to double.
    UnknownEPException
    This exception is thrown if an elementary process was not found to the matching ID although it was needed.
    UnknownIDException
    This exception is thrown if for a string requirement ID no matching requirement could be found in the requirement analysis.
    UnknownReferenceException
    This exception is thrown if an reference on a requirement should be created by a given string as ID but no requirement in the requirement analysis has this ID.
